This is intended as a collection of small use cases exemplifying typical algo problems,
which I'm interested to solve using Java 8, to develop intuition about these APIs.

    minK1:
        Find K smallest elements in unordered "collection"
    officeParty:
        Plan most fun BYOB office party. Party is considered most fun if it has most beers
        to begin with. The trick is, a boss should not show up if his subordinates would,
        so you must plan who shows up knowing how many beers every person plans to bring.